decision_details:
- on a joint proposal made by Hon. Nimal Siripala de Silva, Minister of Irrigation and Water Resources Management; Hon. Basil Rajapaksa, Minister of Economic Development; and  Hon. Janaka Bandara Tennakoon, Minister of Lands and Land Development, Cabinet approval was granted to streamline the procedure of land alienation / disposition so as to ensure that there is a consistent policy on the extent of land that would be made available by the Government and Government Agencies to specific sectors, in the national interest.  Under the proposed procedure - 

*	land alienation for agricultural purposes will be strictly on lease basis for a period not exceeding 35 years;

*	land alienation for industrial purposes will also be strictly on lease basis for a period not exceeding 35 years;

*	land alienation for tourism will be on the basis of 99 year lease and the extent of land will be 30 acres or less; and

*	in case of land required for agricultural or industrial purpose on investments over US $20 million, a suitable long term tenure will be considered.
